This paper deals with decentralized decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of heuristic search is a common technique in both of these fields. Additionally, the paper discusses experimental results and scalability, which are often topics in machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY).
